STATIC DATAMEMBER
static data member is a shared variable by all instantiated objects.
That static data member is usually private
An accessor/mutator function are declared as static

STATIC FUNCTION
A static function can only access static data member
!!! Not sure whether static functions can be const or not
!!! Static function do not have 'this' pointer. They can be called without an instance
i.e: MyClass:MyStaticFunction()
